I’m of two minds on this place. The good is that it’s decent pho, good service, fair pricing, and not too busy like their other location. The not so good is that there isn’t enough fat in the brisket, it’s a little dry, and no fresh jalapeños which I don’t understand why since it’s at the other location. I would give this place 3.5 stars but am debating back and forth about rounding up or down - settled on rounding down but would still come back if I wanted pho in a hurry.

There is nothing about this restaurant stand out more than any other Viet restaurants, but they satisfied my craving for Pho and summer rolls and I have no complaints.  I ordered the grilled chicken pho and it was warm and made me happy. The noodles were cooked well, the grilled chicken was huge, the soup base and broth was flavorful alone, without me adding a whole bunch of Sriracha sauce.  No complaints here, the staff brought the food quickly and didn't motion for me and my friend to leave quickly even if we lingered in the restaurant for a while.
